    "description": "Prince Pipes has an exciting opening for a Manufacturing Engineer at our Mysuru office. Join a company that values innovation, collaboration, and continuous learning.\n\nAbout Prince Pipes:\nPrince Pipes is a leading organization in the On-site sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Ensure compliance with safety regulations and factory acts\n• Train and supervise shop floor workers and supervisors\n• Prepare production cost analysis and efficiency reports\n• Monitor equipment performance and coordinate preventive maintenance\n• Ensure environmental compliance and waste management\n• Conduct root cause analysis for quality rejections and defects\n• Maintain accurate production records and prepare daily reports\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• MBA from a recognized university\n• 3-6 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in TPM\n• Proficiency in FMEA\n• Proficiency in SAP MM/PP\n• Proficiency in Lean Manufacturing\n• Proficiency in ISO 9001\n• Proficiency in Kaizen\n• Proficiency in Project Management\n• Proficiency in GD&T\n\nWork Mode: On-site - Work from our office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Meal coupons and food allowance\n• Annual paid leaves and casual leaves\n• Work-from-home flexibility\n• Employee stock options (ESOPs) for eligible roles\n• Maternity and paternity leave\n• Company-sponsored certifications\n• Salary Range: 7 LPA - 15 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Mysuru, Karnataka, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Prince Pipes!",
